            "title": "BolognaFiere Secures EUR135 Million for Investments and Debt Refinancing",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>(Alliance News) - BolognaFiere Spa announced on Thursday that it has signed a secured financing agreement totaling EUR134.5 million with a pool of leading Italian banks and financial institutions.</p><p></p><!-- Article --><p>\nThe pool includes Intesa Sanpaolo Spa and BPER Banca Spa as global coordinators, bookrunners, and mandated lead arrangers, UniCredit Spa as bookrunner and mandated lead arranger, and Cassa Depositi e Prestiti Spa as mandated lead arranger.</p><p></p><p>\nThe financing, which matures in 2037, has been structured into a EUR55 million capex line to support investments for the construction of the new multifunctional pavilion, a line dedicated to refinancing the current exposure for EUR71.5 million, as well as a EUR8 million revolving line for general cash needs.</p><p></p><p>\nThis operation will allow the group to optimize its financial structure by extending the average debt maturity and reducing its cost.</p><p></p><p>\nBy Giuseppe Fabio Ciccomascolo, Alliance News senior reporter</p><p></p><p>\nComments and questions to redazione@alliancenews.com</p><p></p><p>\nCopyright 2026 Alliance News IS Italian Service Ltd. All rights reserved.</p></div>",
